IN	1 1/2 cups unsalted natural pistachios
IN	1/2 cup chopped pitted dates
IN	1/2 cup chopped dried cherries or dried cranberries
IN	1/2 cup chopped dried apricots
IN	1/4 cup sweet passover wine
IN	1/4 cup pure pomegranate juice
IN	1 tablespoon honey
IN	1 1/2 teaspoons fresh lemon juice
IN	1 teaspoon finely grated orange peel
IN	1 teaspoon ground cinnamon
IN	1/4 teaspoon freshly grated nutmeg
IN	Fresh mint sprigs (for garnish)
PR	Stir pistachios in heavy medium skillet over medium heat until lightly toasted and fragrant, 4 to 5 minutes. Set aside to cool.
PR	Combine dates, cherries, apricots, wine, and juice in medium bowl. Let stand 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Mix in honey, lemon juice, orange peel, and spices. Chop pistachios; mix into haroseth. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.
PR	Garnish haroseth with mint sprigs.
